WEBVTT

00:15:56.880 --> 00:16:00.803
and that he wanted to be
thoroughly used up when he died.

00:16:01.509 --> 00:16:03.200
He went on to write,

00:16:03.224 --> 00:16:06.804
"Life is no brief candle to me

00:16:06.828 --> 00:16:09.022
but a splendid torch

00:16:09.046 --> 00:16:11.831
that I have got hold of for a moment

00:16:11.855 --> 00:16:15.668
before passing to future generations."

00:16:16.532 --> 00:16:21.002
I, too, do not view my life
as a brief candle,

00:16:21.026 --> 00:16:23.781
although I am burning it at both ends.

00:16:23.805 --> 00:16:25.130
(Laughter)

00:16:25.154 --> 00:16:28.469
And I do want it, and me,

00:16:28.493 --> 00:16:33.192
to be thoroughly used up when I die.